      <description>&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To use R in Jupyter Notebook, make sure you have the following things installed in your computer -&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.anaconda.com/products/distribution#windows&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Anaconda distribution&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.r-project.org/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Now, to use R in jupyter notebook, follow the steps -&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Install IRkernal package.&lt;br&gt;
&lt;code&gt;install.packages(&#39;IRkernel&#39;)&lt;/code&gt;&lt;br&gt;
















&lt;figure  &gt;
  &lt;div class=&#34;d-flex justify-content-center&#34;&gt;
